title: Want To Buy:  WTB: Looking to buy ugly guns
postcontent:
Many gun enthusiast have an old beater sitting in the safe or closet. Something they got cheap, freely given, inherited, or neglected/abused in youth. I like to buy these guns and spend time fixing or just enjoying them. I think some "ugly" firearms look just fine as is, as long as they function.

I'm not looking for potentially unsafe or broken beyond simple repair firearms. Just old stuff that someone can't find use for and is reasonably priced. I don't really look to spend more than $150. Especially if I have to find stocks, or parts to refurbish it. I don't pay anywhere near $150 if it's really rough.

I'm fine with a rusted bore as long as I can easily find a replacement online. Surface rusts on firearms is fine. I'm not a collector. I'm a shooter.

Let me know what you have, what you want, and the overall condition of the gun with pics if possible. I don't buy with the intention to resell. I just enjoy minor tinkering and shoot them. 

I like single shot shotguns, 22lr rifles, black powder arms, and inexpensive pistols/derringers. I don't buy anything in 25acp. 

I have a GA weapons permit and do not mind signing a bill of sale.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Sig P245 package (holsters, short trigger, 3 mags, upgrades, parts ammo/reloading)
postcontent:
For sale is a Sig P245.  This is the predecessor to the P220 compact.  I bought this used and have put about 250 rounds through it.  The slide has been professionally refinished; it's black,  and the finish has held up well to the times I've carried it.  The rails are in good shape, with some wear towards the rear, but absolutely no gouging or scratches.  

**Please be aware that the white stuff in the rail/slide area is grease--I like to take good care of my guns**

I replaced the recoil spring 75 rounds ago, so it has a new recoil spring installed.  It also has a Wolff hammer spring installed.  I believe it's an 18b spring, down from the factory 20.  Trigger pull is excellent in both DA and SA, and it hasn't had a problem running stuff with hard primers (two boxes of Tulammo and a box of S&B).  

Included:

Gun, factory case, two 6-round magazines with pinky rest base plate, 1 seven round magazine, new recoil spring (installed), new recoil spring (in package), factory hammer spring, short trigger (installed), Looper brand leather belt slide holster, Remora holster.

For an additional cost, the following is available:

450 count 185 grain Xtreme plated FP in 45ACP
400 count 250 grain Xtreme plated RN in 45ACP
20 count box of Hornady Critical Duty in 45ACP
50 count Blazer Aluminum, 45ACP
50 count Fiocchi (brass case) 45ACP
28 count PPU (brass case) 45ACP


Also a bunch of deprimed brass and at least 100 primed brass if you're into that.  


I'm out of FA10s for the year; if we're going to trade, I'm fine with making a deal now and trading after January 1.  If you're interested in buying only, FFL fee is negotiable.

postcontent:
I bought this pistol several years ago, when they were being imported by Smith & Wesson - note the engraving on the slide. It shoots nice and is comfortable to carry. It's been cared for well with no major scrapes or scuffs.  Some light wear from the occasional carry in a holster, but nothing worn through to the metal. 

Walther PPS (Police Pistol Slim) is short recoil-operated, locked breech pistol that uses modified Browning-type locking with tilting barrel. Frame of the gun is made from impact-resistant polymer. Trigger is double action only, striker fired, with pre-cocked striker system. This system requires a manual recocking (by partial slide retraction) in the case of misfire. Gun is fitted with automated trigger safety and firing pin block. The removable backstrap of the grip, QuickSafe, offers an additional "storage type" safety; once backstrap is removed, the firing pin is automatically decocked and gun is blocked until the backstrap is reinstalled. Sights are low profile, with rear sight adjustable for windage.

Comes with everything pictured: pistol, two different length mags (7 & 8 round), second backstrap, original molded case, lock, and owners manual.
